Surulere is a residential and commercial Local Government Area located on the mainland of Lagos in Lagos State, Nigeria, with an area of 23 km². At the last census in the year 2006, there were 503,975 inhabitants, with a population density of 21,864 inhabitants per square kilometer. 
Overview 
It is home to the Lagos National Stadium (capacity 60,000) built in 1972 for the All-Africa Games. 
The stadium has been allowed to become increasingly dilapidated since 2002.[1] However, in preparation for the 2009 Under 17 FIFA World Cup the facilities were improved, and the event kicked off successfully in October 2009.[2][3] 
