N-Acetylglutamic acid (abbreviated NAcGlu) is biosynthesized from glutamic acid and acetyl-CoA by the enzyme N-acetylglutamate synthase. 
Arginine is the activator for this reaction. 
The reverse reaction, hydrolysis of the acetyl group, is catalyzed by a specific hydrolase. 
NAcGlu activates carbamoyl phosphate synthetase in the urea cycle. 
