"Pilot" or "Meet the Neighbors" is the pilot episode of the American television science fiction sitcom The Neighbors. It was slated to air on the American Broadcasting Company (ABC) on September 26, 2012. The episode was written by Dan Fogelman, and directed by Chris Koch. 
The concept of The Neighbors was devised by Fogelman, who previously wrote the films Cars, Cars 2 and Tangled. 
Although it is a comedy series, its script was cited as potentially being too complex for mainstream American television. 
Fogelman conceived The Neighbors after a visit to the gated community where his mother lived. 
