To address the epidemic which had so far spared the country, in an address to the nation, Ibrahim Boubacar Kéïta, the President of the Republic of Mali declared a state of emergency and instituted a curfew from 9.00 p.m. to 5:00 a.m.[10] 
On 27 March, 7 new positive tests for Coronavirus: Mali rose to 11 cases.[11] 
