Ini Edo (born 23 April 1982) is a Nigerian actress. 
She began her film career in 2000,[1] and has featured in more than 100 movies since her debut.[1] In 2013, she was a judge for the Miss Black Africa UK Pageant.[5] In 2014, Ms. Edo was appointed by the United Nations as aUnited Nations Habitat Youth Envoy.[6] 
