Demi Isaac Oviawe (/ˈdɛmiː ˈaɪzæk əvˈjɑːweɪ/;[2] born 2 November 2000) is a Nigerian-born Irish actress.[3][4] She is best known for her role as Linda Walsh in the 2018 RTÉ/BBC-produced comedy series The Young Offenders.[5] 
Year Title Role Notes 2020 To All My Darlings Adaeze Short[9] 
References 
Oviawe was raised in the Irish town of Mallow by her parents, along with her four younger brothers.[1] Oviawe's parents named her after the actress Demi Moore.[4] In secondary school, Oviawe played camogie and Gaelic Football, and starred in school productions of Beauty and the Beast, Grease and Sister Act.[4] 
Initially, Oviawe planned to train as a secondary school teacher. However, in 2017 she auditioned on YouTube for a role in the TV series The Young Offenders, and won the role of Linda Walsh.[1] 
