Idris Alooma, Idris ibn 'Ali (Alooma), or Idriss Alaoma, (r. 1570–1602/03 or 1580-1617)[1][2][3][4] was Mai (king) of the Kanem-Bornu Empire, located mainly in Chad, Cameroon, Niger and Nigeria. 
His name is more properly written Idris Alawma or Idris Alauma.[5] An outstanding statesman, under his rule Kanem-Bornu touched the zenith of its power. 
Idris is remembered for his military skills, administrative reforms and Islamic piety. 
His feats are mainly known through his chronicler Ahmad bin Fartuwa.[6] 
