Ade Laoye is an actor and performer who was born on 5 April. 
She grew up partly in Ibadan and Lagos. 
She is a graduate of Pennsylvania State University where she studied Theatre Arts.[1] She has numerous credits spanning across theatre, TV, and film. 
She has performed with prestigious theatres such as The Walnut Street Theatre and The Arden Theatre Companies in Philadelphia, and off-Broadway company TheatreWorksUSA in New York City. 
She is also a teaching artist, passionate about using the arts as a tool to educate. 
She is a co-founder of The Real Deal Actors’ Workshop – an intensive training workshop for aspiring actors. 
Notable credits include roles in: Hush (Africa Magic/Victor Sanchez Aghahowa), Castle & Castle (Netflix/EbonyLife Studios), Yelo Pèppè (Sparrow Studios/Shirley Frimpong-Manso), The Tribunal (Golden Effects Pictures/Kunle Afolayan), SARO the Musical (BAP Productions/Bolanle Austen-Peters), Finding Hubby (House Gabriel Studios/Femi Ogunsanwo), and Knockout Blessing (Singularity Media/Dare Olaitan).[2] 
