Afia Schwarzenegger aka Valentina Nana Agyeiwaa (born 14 February 1982, Kumasi, Ghana) is Ghanaian media personality. 
She was the host Okay FM's morning show Yewo krom and UTV Ghana's Kokooko show.[citation needed] She is the CEO of Schwar TV on YouTube;[citation needed] The Ceo of QAS purified water[citation needed], the host of The breakfast show and was appointed as the ambassador of Orphans in Ghana by the Association of Children Homes and Orphanages in Ghana.[citation needed] She is also the founder of Leave2Live foundation, a domestic violence support group and the founder of Owontaa Street Ministry,a non profitable organisation that feeds the less privilege in Ghana[1] Afia has also worked for TV Africa and Kasapa FM.[2] She came in to the lime light through the Afia Schwarzenegger TV series produced by Deloris Frimpong Manso. 
