Kesaoleboga Molotsane (born 8 January 1992)[1] is a South African long-distance runner. 
In 2019, she competed in the senior women's race at the 2019 IAAF World Cross Country Championships held in Aarhus, Denmark.[1] She finished in 42nd place.[1] 
In 2017, she competed in the senior women's race at the 2017 IAAF World Cross Country Championships held in Kampala, Uganda.[2] She finished in 35th place.[2] In the same year, she also competed in the women's 5000 metres event at the 2017 Summer Universiade held in Taipei, Taiwan.[3] She finished in 9th place with a personal best of 16:01.76.[3] 
