Rodrigue Kwizera (born 10 October 1999)[1] is a Burundian long-distance runner. 
In 2019, he competed in the men's 10,000 metres at the 2019 World Athletics Championships held in Doha, Qatar.[1] He finished in 16th place.[1] 
