Greensprings School is a British school in Nigeria. 
It was established in the year 1985, in Lagos. 
It currently operates on the Anthony, Lekki and Ikoyi campuses. 
The school's offers include Crèche, Preschool, Elementary School, Secondary School and Sixth Form. 
The school started as a montessori school in January 1985, with just three (3) pupils, in the heart of Lagos mainland.[citation needed] At the moment, the school has 3 campuses in Lagos, with a population of over 3,500 students.[citation needed] The school is governed by a Board of Governors.[1][2] 
