Eduardo Corrêa Riedel (born in 5 July 1969) is a Brazilian politician and businessman, affiliated to the Brazilian Social Democracy Party, was elected governor of Mato Grosso do Sul in the 2022 elections in Brazil[1]. 
Already held the position of Secretary of State for Infrastructure of Mato Grosso do Sul from February 22, 2022 to January 1, 2023.[2] 
In 2022, he ran in state elections in Mato Grosso do Sul for governor with Barbosinha for vice governor.[3] On October 2, 2022, he had 361,981 votes (25.16%) and went to the second round with candidate Renan Contar.[4][5][6][7] 
Frank Ugochukwu Edwards (born 22 July 1989) is a Nigerian afro-highlife praise and worship singer and songwriter from Enugu State.[1] He is the founder and owner of the record label Rocktown Records, which is home to recording artists such as Edwards himself, Gil, Divine, King BAS, Nkay, David, Dudu and Micah Heavens, among others. 
He lives in Lagos, Nigeria 
