Ayinla is a musical eponymous film based on the life of Ayinla Yusuf popularly known as Ayinla Omowura, an Apala musician who was stabbed to death by his manager named Bayewu in a bar fight on 6 May 1980 at Abeokuta.[2] The film premiered on 13 June 2021 in Lagos and was released to theatres on 18 June 2021.[3][4][4] Directed by Tunde Kelani, the film was set in the 1970s and early 1980s and shot in Abeokuta, Ogun State.[2] Lateef Adedimeji assumed the role of Ayinla, starring alongside Omowumi Dada, Bimbo Manuel, Ade Laoye, Kunle Afolayan, Bimbo Ademoye and Mr Macaroni.[6][7][8] Ayinla is Kelani's first major film since his 2015 release of Dazzling Mirage.[2] The budget for this feature film is officially given as ₦50 Million.[3] 
