Kunle Ajibade (born 28 May 1958) is a Nigerian journalist, editor and author. 
In 1995, along with General Olusegun Obasanjo, and three other journalists, was jailed for life on charges of treason.[1][2] In 1998/1999, he was a Feuchtwanger fellow at the Villa Aurora in Los Angeles.[3] 
Education and early career 
Ajibade holds a Bachelor's in English Studies and a Masters in Literature-In-English from the Obafemi Awolowo University. 
He has worked as Senior Correspondent at The African Concord, Assistant Editor at The African Guardian, and as Executive Editor of TheNEWS and P.M. News. 
