Olukorede S. Yishau is a Nigerian author and journalist. 
He was long listed for the 2021 Nigeria Prize for Literature.[1][2][3] 
Early life and career 
Yishau was born Somolu, Lagos State. 
He studied mass communication at Ambrose Alli University, Ekpoma.[4] He has worked as a journalist at The Source, Tell Magazine and is currently an Associate Editor at The Nation newspaper.[5][6][7] 
Bibliography 
