Prince Tony Momoh (27 April 1939 – 1 February 2021)[1] was a Nigerian journalist and a politician who was Nigerian Minister of Information and Culture (1986–1990) during the military regime of General Ibrahim Babangida.[1][2] 
Birth and education 
Momoh was born on 27 April 1939 in Auchi, Edo state, of Edo origin.[3] He was the 165th child of King Momoh I of Auchi.[4] 
He attended Government School Auchi (1949–1954) and Anglican School Okpe (1954).[3] Momoh was Pupil Teacher at the Anglican School, Auchi (January–December 1955) and Headmaster at the Anglican School, Ubuneke, Ivbiaro, Owan Local Government (January 1958 – December 1959).[2][5] 
Stumai Abdalla is a Tanzanian footballer who plays as a forward for the Tanzanian women's national team.[1][2] In 2019 she was the captain of the national team when they were defending their CECAFA Women's Championship trophy.[3][4] 
